OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAnother dry and bright day with
OL,6,Flong periods of sunshine. A chilly
OL,7,Fstart then becoming quite warm by the
OL,8,Fafternoon. Some patchy mist and low
OL,9,Fcloud may continue to affect the east
OL,10,Fcoast.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FStaying dry through the
OL,13,Fevening with clear spells in the west
OL,14,Fbut low cloud and mist returning to
OL,15,Feastern coasts. Cloud and the odd
OL,16,Flight shower into the north overnight.
OL,17,
OL,18,CSaturday:FStaying dry and warm in the
OL,19,Fwest with prolonged sunny spells.
OL,20,FCooler and cloudier in the northeast
OL,21,Fwith perhaps the odd spot of rain.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
